cted in university programmes. The subject of brain function, studied daily by the neurologist and neuro-surgeon, should gain the interest of non-medical fields concerned with utilizing the mechanism of the mind.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aCybernetics. 7aEDUCATION / Educational Psychology.2bisacsh1 aFeindel, William, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFeindel, William, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHoffer, A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLeddy, J.F., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPenfield, Wilder, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPorter, Arthur, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSpinks, J.W.T., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press eBook-Package Archive 1933-1999z978311049094740uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978148759517340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781487595173423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781487595173.jpg  a978-3-11-049094-7  University of Toronto Press eBook-Package Archive 1933-1999c1933d1999  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK